      "noteButton": "Diphthongs are generally treated as long vowels. However, when either οι or αι occur at the end of the word, though they are pronounced the same, they are treated as short vowels for accent purposes. ἄνθρωποι (οι is final, therefore short); ἀνθρώποις (οι is not final, therefore long). (Summers/Sawyer, p. 4)"
